ard against which all goodness is to be measured. ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0455  Tc 2.7685  Tw (It is important to understand this in the context of the law that God) Tj301.44 0  TD -0.0919  Tc 2.3719  Tw ( had just given to Moses. The) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-301.44 -11.52  TD -0.0662  Tc 0.3697  Tw (commandments were not just rules to determine the limits of human behavior, they were expressions of the ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0752  Tc 1.2074  Tw (character of God. That is why it can be said that the law is good. We tend to see laws as restrictions of ) TjT* -0.1197  Tc 0.7197  Tw (human liberty. ) Tj62.4 0  TD -0.047  Tc 0.8337  Tw (It is true that God\222s goodness restricts evil, but it also means that God blesses us and fills ) Tj-62.4 -11.52  TD -0.0692  Tc 1.0355  Tw (our lives with His goodness. James puts it this way: \223Every good and perfect gift is from above, coming ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0735  Tc -0.0465  Tw (down from the Father of the heavenly lights, who does not) Tj231.36 0  TD -0.1075  Tc -0.0125  Tw ( change like shifting shadows.\224) Tj122.88 4.32  TD /F0 6.72  Tf0  Tc 0  Tw (790) Tj10.08 -4.32  TD /F0 10.08  Tf-0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-364.32 -11.52  TD ( ) Tj36 0  TD -0.0572  Tc 0.2343  Tw (Goodness is an absolute that can only be found in God, but at the same time it is a characteristic to ) Tj-36 -11.52  TD -0.084  Tc 0.9774  Tw (which we can relate. We experience goodness as something that agrees with us, that fills and satisfies us. ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.1214  Tc 2.4014  Tw (When we encou) Tj68.16 0  TD -0.0542  Tc 1.9954  Tw (nter goodness we realize that this is what we were made for; it is the reason for our) Tj0  Tc -0.12  Tw ( ) Tj-68.16 -11.52  TD -0.1009  Tc 0.8209  Tw (existence. In God\222s goodness we find all His perfections of love, kindness, gentleness and beauty wrapped ) Tj0 -11.52  TD -0.0658  Tc 0.9058  Tw (together. And, although Moses was not able to experience God\222s g) Tj272.64 0  TD -0.0293  Tc 0.3207  Tw (oodnes